{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0167a3zPyPMTSdxKiHR1T1Fa","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pods are still in CrashLoopBackOff and the PVCs are in \"Terminating\" state. The PVCs are terminating because the pods still exist (or were just deleted but haven't been removed from the PVC finalizer list).\n\nThe pods are in CrashLoopBackOff - they were recreated by the StatefulSet controller. This is good in a sense, but they're using the OLD PVCs (which are now terminating). Wait, no - the pods are referencing the PVCs that are \"Terminating\". \n\nActually, I need the pods to be DELETED first so the PVCs can be deleted, and then the StatefulSet will recreate both pods AND PVCs fresh.\nThe PVC finalizer is blocking deletion while the pod still references it, and the StatefulSet keeps spinning up new pods whenever I delete them. So when I delete a pod, the StatefulSet immediately recreates it, which means the PVC can never finish terminating.\n\nThe new pods are actually running in CrashLoopBackOff, which means they're binding to the PVCs somehow—possibly the terminating ones are still accessible, or there's a race condition where the PVCs get deleted before the new pods try to mount them. I need to check what state the newly recreated pods are actually in. might still be using it, and if so, keeps the finalizer. So when the StatefulSet recreates the pod, it tries to bind to the same PVC, which is now \"Terminating\" — and that's probably causing the new pod to fail to mount properly, leading to the CrashLoopBackOff.\n\nThe solution is to scale down the StatefulSet to 3 replicas temporarily, letting those two PVCs fully terminate without any pod claiming them, then scale back up to 5 so fresh PVCs get created.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":618,"cache_read_input_tokens":54708,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":618},"output_tokens":28,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"367501ed-e4a5-4000-b239-5419541c94df","uuid":"3a8b7cbd-c5e0-432f-9fc3-0a138cd775d4","request_id":"req_011CcP4gavQzhBMh6reTZCue"}
