{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Mr79MB6zepzREAZKzSvtnj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The keyFile content is IDENTICAL on both nodes. So the password is the same. Yet, the SCRAM authentication fails with \"storedKey mismatch\".\n\nSince `local.system.users` is EMPTY on the primary (no `__system` user stored there), and the keyFile is the same on all nodes, what determines the `__system@local` authentication credentials?\n\nLet me look at this from another angle. The \"storedKey\" in SCRAM is stored SOMEWHERE. Since it's not in `local.system.users`, maybe it's in-memory or derived on-the-fly.\nIf the stored key is derived on-the-fly from the keyFile with a random salt, then each instance would generate different keys, which wouldn't work across nodes. There must be some shared key derivation state. I'm wondering if this relates to the `admin.system.keys` collection, which stores intra-cluster authentication tokens in MongoDB.\n\nThese tokens are generated when the replica set initializes and shared across members via oplog replication. New members haven't synced yet, so they don't have these keys—creating a chicken-and-egg problem where they need the keys to authenticate but can't fetch them without authentication. I tried accessing `admin.system.keys` with the admin user but wasn't authorized, so I'm checking whether the `clusterAdmin` role grants access to system keys.\n\nLooking more carefully at the SCRAM authentication failure, the real issue is that `local.system.users` is empty on all existing members, meaning the `__system` user doesn't actually exist there—so authentication is failing at the stored key comparison stage.\n\nBut the existing members can authenticate to each other somehow, which suggests they're using a different mechanism entirely, probably `admin.system.keys` that was established during `rs.initiate()` and propagated through the oplog. The new members haven't received these keys yet, which is why they're stuck.\n\nLet me compare what's actually in the local database between existing and new members to figure out what's different.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":344,"cache_read_input_tokens":93212,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":344},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"367501ed-e4a5-4000-b239-5419541c94df","uuid":"01e23f00-aa8d-43dc-875b-a840ab871c4c","request_id":"req_011CcP5mMpNoA5fdyuzPPZGy"}
